 <h4>Solution by Runge-Kutta RK4 method (explicit)</h4>
 <p>For that purpose, the II order equation is reduced to the following system of I order equations</p>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <var>θ′</var>
   =
   <var>ω</var>
  </span>
  and
  <span class="eq">
   <var>ω′</var>
   =
   <span class="dvc">
    <var>g</var>
    <span class="dvl">
    </span>
    <var>l</var>
   </span>
   ·
   <b>sin</b>
   ( -
   <var>θ</var>
   )
  </span>
 </p>
 <p>The solution will be performed iteratively</p>
 <p>
  Step size -
  <span class="eq">
   <var>h</var>
   = 0.02
   <i>s</i>
  </span>
 </p>
 <p>
  Number of steps -
  <span class="eq">
   <var>n</var>
   =
   <span class="dvc">
    <var>t</var>
    <sub>max</sub>
    <span class="dvl">
    </span>
    <var>h</var>
   </span>
   =
   <span class="dvc">
    11
    <i>s</i>
    <span class="dvl">
    </span>
    0.02
    <i>s</i>
   </span>
   = 550
  </span>
 </p>
 <p>
  For each time step
  <span class="eq">
   <var>n</var>
   = 550
  </span>
  the values for the next step will be obtained by using the following equstions
 </p>
 <table class="eq" style="margin-left:24pt;">
  <tr>
   <td>First step (k₁) -</td>
   <td>
    <span class="eq">
     <var>k</var>
